      Meanwhile in Berlin
   =20
 =20
He=E2=80=99s going to mount a hostile takeover of Berghain:Elon Musk dived =
into Berlin=E2=80=99s famed fetish and electronic music scene at the weeken=
d in a club crawl that ended abruptly in front of the Berghain techno templ=
e, prompting speculation that he had been denied entry.No, I kid, but there=
 is an important=C2=A0question here, which is, did the bouncer know who he =
was? When Elon Musk arrived at the door of Berghain, did the bouncer look a=
t him and think =E2=80=9Cthis is a dork=E2=80=9D and turn him away for that=
 reason, or did the bouncer instead think =E2=80=9Cthis is Elon Musk, the r=
ichest person in the world=E2=80=9D and turn him away for=C2=A0that=C2=A0re=
ason? Like probably there are a lot of nightclubs that would love to have E=
lon Musk come party, because he is famous and has a lot of money, but surel=
y Berghain isn=E2=80=99t one of them? Elon Musk partying at Berghain will n=
ot raise Berghain=E2=80=99s profile or make it cooler, and he can=E2=80=99t=
 spend=C2=A0that=C2=A0much money, but=C2=A0turning away Elon Musk=C2=A0is=
=C2=A0obviously great for Berghain=E2=80=99s fame and coolness. Still, both=
 possibilities are wonderful, and I suppose they could both be true sequent=
ially:Elon Musk: What=E2=80=99s happening my man.Sven, Berghain=E2=80=99s =
=E2=80=9Ciconic bouncer=E2=80=9D who =E2=80=9Clooks for outfits, aesthetic =
and vibes=E2=80=9D:=C2=A0[Looks at outfit, aesthetic and vibes] You can=E2=
=80=99t come in.Elon: Do you know who I am, I am Elon Musk, the richest per=
son in the world, I have spaceships and stuff.Sven: [Googles] So you are.El=
on: So!Sven: Now you really can=E2=80=99t come in.
