      Things happen
   =20
 =20
Zeke Faux profiles  Sam Bankman-Fried. Trump-Tied  Social Media SPAC Slides=
 After Key Executives Quit.=C2=A0Judge Tosses California Law Mandating Dive=
rsity on Boards.=C2=A0Starbucks Suspends Share Buybacks as Howard Schultz R=
eturns as CEO.=C2=A0Tom Brady joins firm launched by disgraced PR guru Decl=
an Kelly.=C2=A0In Defense of Bitcoin Maximalism (by Vitalk Buterin on April=
 1).If you'd like to get=C2=A0Money=C2=A0Stuff=C2=A0in handy email form, ri=
ght in your inbox, please=C2=A0subscribe at this link. Or you can subscribe=
 to Money Stuff and other great Bloomberg newsletters here. Thanks![1] This=
 is a joke, and you can easily find Twitter board members who tweet. But ot=
her than *maybe* Jack Dorsey, I think Musk would clearly be the first true =
*poster* on Twitter=E2=80=99s board. Like everyone else tweets as part of a=
 professional communications strategy. Musk tweets because he loves tweetin=
g.[2] Another weird aspect: The filing came out today, April 4, and lists M=
arch 14 as the =E2=80=9Cdate of event which requires filing.=E2=80=9D If th=
at means what it intuitively seems like =E2=80=94=C2=A0that is, March 14 is=
 the date on which Musk acquired more than 5% of Twitter=E2=80=99s stock, r=
equiring a 13G filing =E2=80=94=C2=A0then =E2=80=A6=C2=A0isn=E2=80=99t the =
filing late?=C2=A0[3] Twitter trades an average of about 16.4 million share=
s a day,=C2=A0so it would take a week to sell all of Musk=E2=80=99s shares =
*if he was 100% of volume*; a more reasonable pace would be 10-20% of volum=
e, meaning a month or two. But those volume numbers are pre-Musk-announceme=
nt, and his filing has boosted the volume as well as the price; by 11 a.m. =
today Twitter had traded more than 110 million shares.[4] The amendment req=
uirements for Schedule 13G require prompt disclosure if you reduce your sta=
ke by more than five percentage points. So basically he could sell 4.9% wit=
hout disclosure but then would have to bang out the rest fast.
