ctivist would say, and if other shareholders agreed with her plans then she=
=E2=80=99d win a proxy fight and replace the managers and the system would =
move toward the perfect goal of maximizing profits.</p><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">When I started in corporate law and finance, this consensus had be=
en dominant for decades and felt very, very stable. In 2022 it seems like a=
 weird historical blip, a few decades (1980 to 2010?) when everyone fell in=
to a radically oversimplified understanding of what companies are. Now ever=
yone =E2=80=94=C2=A0even big-company CEOs =E2=80=94=C2=A0talks about =E2=80=
=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27253239.266604=
